<p>This function takes a string and makes it to pirate language.</p>  <p>But it doesn't work when I want it to take pirate language and return the normal language.</p>  <pre><code>  :- dynamic (lang/2).   lang([],[]).   lang(Text, Text2) :-     [Head|Tail] = Text,     lang(Tail,X2),     (member(Head,[101,97,105,111,117,121])         -&gt; append([Head],X2,Text2)         ; append([Head,111,Head],X2,Text2)         ). </code></pre>  <p>it works when calling <code>lang([list of hex codes for chars], X).</code> But it doesn't work with <code>lang(X, [answer from above])</code>.</p>